__text: Measuring voltage indicates the place where the electrical state changes due to a damaged bulb.
Measuring voltage indicates the place where the electrical state changes due to a gap.
Measuring voltage indicates whether two terminals are connected to each other.
Measuring voltage indicates whether two terminals are separated by a gap.
A zero voltage means that the terminals are connected.
A non-zero voltage means that the terminals are not connected.
A zero voltage means that the terminals are not separated by a gap.
A non-zero voltage means that the terminals are separated by a gap.
A non-zero voltage means that there is a damaged bulb.
A non-zero voltage means that there is a gap
A zero voltage means that there is no damaged bulb.
A zero voltage means that there is no gap
A non-zero voltage means that the terminals have different electrical states.
A zero voltage means that the terminals have the same electrical state.
